HEADWORD: Anophyte
<hw>An"o*phyte</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*f⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'a`nw</grk> upward (fr. <grk>'ana`</grk> up) +
<grk>fyto`n</grk> a plant, <grk>fy`ein</grk> to grow.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A moss or mosslike plant which cellular stems,
having usually an upward growth and distinct leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

